@*
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    BnCheckbox — Phase 7.3 Task 1.2 (design decision 1 + 2), authored in
    .razor (the 7.1 recipe: everything new is .razor).

    Emits the `checkbox` element → NodeType 8 (new in 7.3 — a wire-vocabulary
    extension, not an ABI change). Android: MaterialCheckBox. iOS: UISwitch —
    design decision 2, the RECORDED "renders natively, not identically"
    divergence: iOS has no native checkbox (UIKit's toggle is UISwitch; React
    Native ships only Switch for the same reason), so BnCheckbox and BnSwitch
    are semantically identical on iOS and visually distinct only on Android.
    Same wire, same events, same frames — different pixels. A custom-drawn
    iOS checkbox would buy pixel parity at the cost of not being native,
    against the project's thesis.

    THE WIRE:
      • `value` prop — "true"/"false", ALWAYS emitted (the BnInput posture:
        the host prop exists from mount, no shell-side default to mirror).
      • `change` event — the EXISTING wire, payload exactly "true"/"false".
        The attach is UNCONDITIONAL, like BnInput's (the bind pair is the
        component's whole point; contrast BnScroll.OnScroll, which attaches
        on-subscribe because it is optional telemetry). A DISABLED checkbox
        still attaches — the host widget is disabled, so it never dispatches
        (Gates 2/3 assert "disabled controls dispatch nothing" on-device);
        keeping the attach unconditional keeps the wire shape independent of
        Enabled, exactly as BnInput's is.
      • `enabled` prop — only when false (BnButton's boolean-attribute
        semantics; leaving re-emits null → host restores its default).
      • The bind-loop guard: a PROGRAMMATIC Checked set re-renders to an
        UpdateProp and must NOT re-fire change — .NET-side that is structural
        (CheckedChanged is only invoked from the change handler); host-side
        it is the applyingBatch listener guard (Android, the 4.2 TextWatcher
        lesson) / setOn-fires-nothing VERIFIED per control (iOS, Gate 3).

    A leaf with a FIXED INTRINSIC SIZE via the measure func (by NodeType —
    the 6.1 law). The intrinsic size is the platform's own (a UISwitch is
    51×31pt, a MaterialCheckBox is whatever Material says): frame parity
    applies to LAYOUT — declared sizes and placement — never to intrinsic
    control sizes (design §Measurement). The flex ITEM surface below is
    BnScroll's (how this control is placed IN ITS PARENT); it is not a
    container and has no children.

    GARBAGE IS LOUD (the 7.2 scroll-payload pattern): a change payload that
    is not exactly "true"/"false" is a SHELL contract violation, not user
    input — the handler throws FormatException, the dispatch window surfaces
    it as export rc 2, and no silently-wrong bool reaches the app.
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@
<checkbox value="@(Checked ? "true" : "false")"
          enabled="@(Enabled ? null : "false")"
          backgroundColor="@BackgroundColor"
          margin="@Margin"
          alignSelf="@AlignSelf.ToStyleValue()"
          flexGrow="@Grow.ToStyleValue()"
          flexShrink="@Shrink.ToStyleValue()"
          flexBasis="@Basis"
          width="@Width"
          height="@Height"
          minWidth="@MinWidth"
          maxWidth="@MaxWidth"
          minHeight="@MinHeight"
          maxHeight="@MaxHeight"
          position="@Position.ToStyleValue()"
          top="@Top"
          right="@Right"
          bottom="@Bottom"
          left="@Left"
          @onchange="HandleChange" />

@code {
    /// <summary>The checked state. Always emitted (as <c>"true"</c>/<c>"false"</c>)
    /// so the host prop exists from mount.</summary>
    [Parameter] public bool Checked { get; set; }

    /// <summary>Raised with the new state on a host change event — the
    /// write-back half of the <c>@bind-Checked</c> pair.</summary>
    [Parameter] public EventCallback<bool> CheckedChanged { get; set; }

    /// <summary>False disables the host widget (it renders disabled and
    /// dispatches nothing). Default true.</summary>
    [Parameter] public bool Enabled { get; set; } = true;

    // ── The flex ITEM surface (BnScroll's — how this leaf sits in its parent) ─

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.BackgroundColor"/>
    [Parameter] public string? BackgroundColor { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.Margin"/>
    [Parameter] public string? Margin { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.AlignSelf"/>
    [Parameter] public FlexAlign? AlignSelf { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.Grow"/>
    [Parameter] public float? Grow { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.Shrink"/>
    [Parameter] public float? Shrink { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.Basis"/>
    [Parameter] public string? Basis { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.Width"/>
    [Parameter] public string? Width { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.Height"/>
    [Parameter] public string? Height { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.MinWidth"/>
    [Parameter] public string? MinWidth { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.MaxWidth"/>
    [Parameter] public string? MaxWidth { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.MinHeight"/>
    [Parameter] public string? MinHeight { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.MaxHeight"/>
    [Parameter] public string? MaxHeight { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.Position"/>
    [Parameter] public FlexPosition? Position { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.Top"/>
    [Parameter] public string? Top { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.Right"/>
    [Parameter] public string? Right { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.Bottom"/>
    [Parameter] public string? Bottom { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.Left"/>
    [Parameter] public string? Left { get; set; }

    private Task HandleChange(ChangeEventArgs e)
        => CheckedChanged.InvokeAsync(ParseBoolPayload(e.Value?.ToString(), "checkbox"));

    /// <summary>Strict wire parse — exactly <c>"true"</c>/<c>"false"</c>
    /// (ordinal; the shells emit these two literals and nothing else). A
    /// missing or different payload is a SHELL contract violation: throw, and
    /// the dispatch window surfaces it as a loud rc-2 fault (the 7.2
    /// scroll-offset pattern) instead of dispatching a silently-wrong
    /// bool.</summary>
    internal static bool ParseBoolPayload(string? payload, string control) => payload switch
    {
        "true" => true,
        "false" => false,
        _ => throw new FormatException(
            $"{control} change dispatch carried '{payload ?? "<null>"}' — the wire contract " +
            "requires exactly \"true\" or \"false\""),
    };
}
